EAST CHICAGO, Ind. (AP) — A 7-year-old boy was fatally shot early Tuesday in East Chicago, the Lake County Coroner’s Office said.Jermiah Moore died from a gunshot wound in a homicide, the coroner’s office said in a news release.Around 1 a.m., East Chicago police received several calls about shots fired , and the boy was transported to the emergency room at St. Catherine’s Hospital, where he was pronounced dead at 1:28 a.m., the news release said.The boy was identified by family members, the release said. His address was unknown, it said.Additional details on the circumstances surrounding the shooting were not immediately released.